quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  2,283,"But if you are upon a journey, and you cannot find a scribe, then let a pledge be taken. But if one of you trust another, then let him who is trusted surrender his trust, and let him fear Allah his Lord, and conceal not testimony, for he who conceals it"
  2,284,"Allah´s is what is in heaven and in the earth, and if you show what is in your souls, or hide it, Allah will call you to account; and He forgives whom He will, and punishes whom He will, for Allah is Able to do all things"
  2,285,"The Messenger believes in what is sent down to him from his Lord, and so do the believers. Each believes in Allah, and His angels, and His Scriptures, and His Messengers, - We make no distinction between any of His Messengers - and they say, \"We hear"
  2,286,"Allah will not require of the soul beyond its capacity. It shall have what it has earned, and it shall owe what it deserves. \"Our Lord, condemn us not, if we forget or miss the mark; Our Lord, load us not with a burden as Thou hast loaded those befor"
  3,1,ALIF LAM MIM
  3,2,"Allah, there is no God but He, the Living, the Self-Subsisting, Eternal"
  3,3,"It is He who has sent down to you the Scripture with truth, confirming what was revealed before it, and has revealed the Torah and the Gospel before this for the guidance of mankind, and has revealed the Discrimination (Criterion)"
  3,4,"Verily, those who disbelieve in the signs of Allah, for them is a severe penalty, for Allah is Mighty and Avenging"
  3,5,"Verily, from Allah, there is nothing hidden in the earth, nor in heaven"
  3,6,"He it is who fashions you in the womb as He pleases. There is no God but He, the Mighty, the Wise"
  3,7,"He it is who has revealed to you the Book, in which there are some verses that are Basic (decisive, or of established meaning) they are the mother (foundation) of the Book; and others are allegorical. But as for those in whose heart is perversity, they fo"
  3,8,"O Lord! Pervert not our heart after Thou hast guided us, and grant us mercy from Thee, for Thou, only Thou art the Bestower (the Giver of Bounties)"
  3,9,"O Lord! It is Thou Who gathers together mankind unto the Day wherein is no doubt. Verily, Allah will not depart from His promise"
  3,10,"Verily, their wealth shall not help the faithless, nor their children, against Allah at all; they will be fuel for the fire"
  3,11,"As was the case with Pharaoh´s people and their predecessors: they said Our signs were lies, and Allah seized them for their sins, for Allah is severe in punishment"
  3,12,"Say to those who disbelieve, \"Soon you shall be overcome and driven together to Hell, an evil bed will it be"
  3,13,"You already have had a sign in the two parties who met (at the battle of Badr); one party fighting in the way of Allah, the other disbelieving; these saw, with their very eyes, twice the number as themselves. Thus Allah strengthens with His help tho"
  3,14,"Beautiful unto men is the life of lust for women, and children, and heaps of hoarded gold and silver, and of horses well bred, and cattle, and well tilled land; these are the comforts for the life of this world; but Allah, with Him is the more excellent r"